
                      Magic Mushroom Shareware Demo
                      *****************************
 
               Designed and programmed by A.Lavoipierre


                         Type GO to run the demo



        
INSTRUCTIONS
------------

        When you start the game, you will be presented with a zone select 
screen. After choosing a zone, you will then see the main title screen
(just press any key to get past this). The object of this "platform" game 
is to guide a red and white spotted mushroom around a number of levels and 
collect special bonus gems. Some levels have treacherous spikes and evil 
little grey toadstools which get in your way, so you will need sharp reflexes 
and a logical mind to complete the game.
        There are about 50 levels in this test version - to complete each you
must collect 5 gems. The gems are distributed randomly across the level.
When you collect one, another appears until you have collected all 5. 
To make things difficult, you die if you collide with one of the grey
toadstools or if you fall off the bottom of the screen. 
        The controls are:
                ALT jump
                LEFT SHIFT move left
                RIGHT SHIFT move right

        Note that these keys are dynamic - so the longer you hold one down,
the faster you will move in a certain direction. There are a few other
features built into the control system, but they will become apparent when
you play the game.

        To quit the game, press escape.


PROGRAM INFORMATION
-------------------

        This is a shareware version of Magic Mushroom, so while it can be
distributed freely, I would like to make a few points: 

1)      You can register for the small fee of 10 pounds (or US equivalent),
 and for this you will get another 50 extra levels with entirely new graphics
 and a mouse driven full screen level editor (allows you to create your own 
 "episodes"). 
